  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,4,"My dear brothers and sisters and friends throughout the world, I offer my personal welcome to this general conference. We gather as a great global family desiring to worship our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ. Thank you for joining with us."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,5,This last year has been one for the record books. No doubt we have each learned things we did not know previously. Some lessons that I knewbeforehave been written on my heart in new and instructive ways.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,6,"For example, Iknowfor sure that the Lord directs the affairs of His Church. He said, “I will show [you] that I am able to do mine own work.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,7,"Often, my counselors and I have watched through tear-brimmed eyes as He has interceded in extremely challenging circumstances after we had done our best and could do no more. We do indeed stand all amazed."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,8,"I also understand better now what He meant when He said, “Behold, I will hasten my work in its time.”Over and over again I have rejoiced as He has directed and executed the hastening of His work—even during a global pandemic."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,9,"My dear brothers and sisters, the strength of the Church lies in the efforts and ever-growing testimonies of its members. Testimonies are best cultivated in the home. During this past year,manyof you have dramatically increased the study of the gospel in your homes. I thank you, and your children will thank you."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,10,The huge project to renovate the Salt Lake Temple continues. From my office I have a front-row seat to watch the work taking place on the temple plaza.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,11,"As I have watched workers dig out old tree roots,plumbing, wiring, and a leaky fountain, I have thought about the need for each of us to remove, with the Savior’s help, the old debris in our lives."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,12,"The gospel of Jesus Christisa gospel of repentance.Because of the Savior’s Atonement, His gospel provides an invitation to keep changing, growing, and becoming more pure. It is a gospel of hope, of healing, and of progress. Thus, the gospel is a message ofjoy! Our spirits rejoice with every small step forward we take."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,13,"Part of the gathering of Israel, and a very important part, is the charge for us as a people to beworthyandwillingto help prepare the world for the Second Coming of the Lord."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,14,"As we listen to the messages that have been carefully prepared by our leaders under the direction of the Holy Ghost, I invite you to pray to identify the debris you should remove from your life so you can become more worthy."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,15,"I love you, my dear brothers and sisters, and testify that our Heavenly Father and His Beloved Son know and love you individually. They stand ready to assist you in every step forward you take. Welcome to general conference and to the privilege of hearing the voice of the Lord. In the name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,16,Notes
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,17,"2 Nephi 27:21."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,18,"Doctrine and Covenants 88:73."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/11nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,19,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 13:1."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,4,"Throughout the ages, God has spoken through His servants, the prophets.This morning we have had the privilege to hear the prophet of God speak to all the world. We love you, President Nelson, and I encourage everyone everywhere to study and heed your words."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,5,"Before I reached my 12th birthday, our family had been forced twice to flee our home and start over amid the chaos, fear, and uncertainties caused by war and political division. It was an anxious time for me, but it must have been terrifying for my beloved parents."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,6,"My mother and father shared little about this burden with us four children. They bore the strain and suffering as best they could. The fear must have been oppressive, consuming their hours and dampening their hope."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,7,This time of bleakness after World War II left its mark upon the world. It left its mark upon me.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,8,"Back then, in the solitude of my loneliest hours, I often wondered, “Is there any hope left in the world?”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,9,"As I pondered this question, I thought about our young American missionaries who served among us during those years. They had left the safety of their homes half a world away and traveled to Germany—land of their recent enemies—to offer divine hope to our people. They came not to blame, lecture, or shame. They willingly gave of their young lives without thought of earthly gain, wanting only to help others find the joy and peace they had experienced."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,10,"To me, these young men and women were perfect. I am sure they had flaws, but not to me. I will always think of them as being bigger than life—angels of light and glory, ministers of compassion, goodness, and truth."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,11,"While the world was drowning in cynicism, bitterness, hatred, and fear, the example and teachings of these young people filled me with hope. The gospel message they offered transcended politics, history, grudges, grievances, and personal agendas. It gave divine answers to important questions we had during these difficult times."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,12,"The message was that God lived and cared about us, even in these hours of turmoil, confusion, and chaos. That He actually appeared in our time to restore truth and light—His gospel and His Church. That He speaks to prophets again; that God is among us—and is personally involved in our lives and actively guiding His children."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,13,"It is astonishing what we can learn when we look a little closer at our Heavenly Father’s plan of salvation and exaltation, the plan of happiness, for His children. When we feel insignificant, cast off, and forgotten, we learn that we may be assured that God has not forgotten us—in fact, that He offers to all His children something unimaginable: to become “heirs of God, and joint-heirs with Christ.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,14,What does this mean?
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,15,"That we will live forever, receive a fulness of joy,and have the potential to “inherit thrones, kingdoms, principalities, and powers.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,16,It is so humbling to know that this magnificent and supernal future is possible—not because of who we are but because of who God is.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,17,"Knowing this, how could we ever murmur or remain embittered? How could we ever keep our eyes on the ground when the King of kings invites us to take flight into an unimaginable future of divine happiness?"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,18,"Because of God’s perfect love for us and the eternal sacrifice of Jesus Christ, our sins—both great and small—can be blotted out and remembered no more.We can stand before Him pure, worthy, and sanctified."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,19,"My heart overflows with gratitude for my Heavenly Father. I realize that He has not doomed His children to stumble through mortality without hope for a bright and eternal future. He has provided instructions that reveal the way back to Him. And at the center of it all isHis Beloved Son, Jesus Christ,and His sacrifice for us."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,20,"The Savior’s infinite Atonement completely changes the way we mayview our transgressions and imperfections. Instead of dwelling on them and feeling irredeemable or hopeless, we can learn from them and feel hopeful.The cleansing gift of repentance allows us to leave our sins behind and emerge a new creature."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,21,"Because of Jesus Christ, our failures do not have to define us. They can refine us."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,22,"Like a musician rehearsing scales, we can see our missteps, flaws, and sins as opportunities for greater self-awareness, deeper and more honest love for others, and refinement through repentance."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,23,"If we repent, mistakes do not disqualify us. They are part of our progress."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,24,"We are all infants compared to the beings of glory and grandeur we are designed to become. No mortal being advances from crawling to walking to running without frequent stumbles, bumps, and bruises. That is how we learn."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,25,"If we earnestly keep practicing, always striving to keep God’s commandments, and committing our efforts to repenting, enduring, and applying what we learn, line upon line, we will gather light into our souls.And though we may not fully comprehend our full potential now, “we know that, when [the Savior] shall appear,” we will see His countenance in us and “shall see him as he is.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,26,What a glorious promise!
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,27,"Yes, the world is in turmoil. And yes, we have weaknesses. But we do not need to hang our heads in despair, because we can trust God, we can trust His Son, Jesus Christ, and we can accept the gift of the Spirit to guide us on this path toward a life filled with joy and divine happiness."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,28,"I often have wondered, What would Jesus teach and do if He were among us today?"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,29,"After the Resurrection, Jesus Christ fulfilled His promise to visit His “other sheep.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,30,"The Book of Mormon: Another Testament of Jesus Christ speaks of such an appearance to the people on the American continent. We have this precious record as a tangible witness of the Savior’s work."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,31,"The people of the Book of Mormon lived on the other side of the globe—their histories, cultures, and political climates were vastly different from the people Jesus taught during His mortal ministry. And yet He taught them many of the same things He taught in the Holy Land."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,32,Why would He do that?
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,33,The Savior always teaches timeless truths. They apply to people of every age and in any circumstance.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,34,His message was and is a message of hope and belonging—a testimony that God our Heavenly Father has not abandoned His children.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,35,That God is among us!
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,36,"Two hundred years ago, the Savior again returned to earth. Together with God the Father, He appeared to a 14-year-old Joseph Smith and ushered in the Restoration of the gospel and the Church of Jesus Christ. From that day forward, the heavens opened, and heavenly messengers descended from halls of immortal glory. Lightand knowledge poured forth from the celestial throne."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,37,The Lord Jesus Christ spoke once again to the world.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,38,What did He say?
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,39,"To our blessing, many of His words are recorded in the Doctrine and Covenants—available to anyone in the world who wishes to read and study them. How priceless are these words to us today!"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,40,"And we should not be surprised to find that the Savior again teaches the core message of His gospel: “Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, with all thy might, mind, and strength; and in the name of Jesus Christ thou shalt serve him.”He inspires us to seek Godand live by the teachings He has revealed to His servants, the prophets."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,41,He teaches us to love one anotherand to be “full of charity towards all men.”
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,42,"He invites us to be His hands, to go about doing good.“Let us not love in word … but in deed and in truth.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,43,"He challenges us to heed His great commission: to love, to share, to invite all to His gospel and His Church."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,44,He commands us to build holy temples and to enter and serve there.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,45,"He teaches us to become His disciples—that our hearts should not strive for personal power, wealth, approval, or position. He teaches us to “lay aside the things of this world, and seek for the things of a better.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,46,"He urges us to seek joy, enlightenment, peace, truth, happiness,and the promise of immortality and eternal life."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,47,"Let us take this a step further. Suppose Jesus came to your ward, to your branch, or to your home today. What would that be like?"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,48,He would see right into your heart. Outward appearances would lose their importance. He would know you as you are. He would know your heart’s desires.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,49,The meek and the humble He would lift.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,50,The sick He would heal.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,51,The doubting He would infuse with faith and courage to believe.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,52,He would teach us to open our hearts to God and reach out to others.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,53,"He would recognize and honor honesty, humility, integrity, faithfulness, compassion, and charity."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,54,"One look into His eyes and we would never be the same. We wouldbe forever changed. Transformed by the profound realization that, indeed, God is among us."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,55,"I look back with kindness on the young man I was during my growing-up years. If I could go back in time, I would comfort him and tell him to stay on the right track and keep searching. And I would ask him to invite Jesus Christ into his life, for God is among us!"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,56,"To you, my dear brothers and sisters, my dear friends, and to all who are searching for answers, truth, and happiness, I do offer the same counsel: keep searching with faith and patience."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,57,"Ask, and you will receive. Knock, and it will be opened unto you.Trust the Lord."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,58,In our daily life it is our paramount task and blessed opportunity to encounter God.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,59,"As we set aside pride and approach His throne with a broken heart and a contrite spirit,He will draw near to us."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,60,"As we seek to follow Jesus Christ and walk the path of discipleship, line upon line, the day will come that we will experience that unimaginable gift of receiving a fulness of joy."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,61,"My beloved friends, your Heavenly Father loves you with a perfect love. He has proven His love in endless ways, but above all by giving His Only Begotten Son as a sacrifice and as a gift to His children to make the return to our heavenly parents a reality."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,62,"I bear witness that our Heavenly Father lives, that Jesus Christ leads His Church, that President Russell M. Nelson is His prophet."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,63,"I extend to you my love and blessing at this joyful Easter season. Open your hearts to our Savior and Redeemer, no matter your circumstances, trials, sufferings, or mistakes; you can know that He lives, that He loves you, and that because of Him, you will never be alone."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,64,God is among us.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,65,"Of this I testify and bear witness in the sacred name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,66,Notes
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,67,"SeeAmos 3:7."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,68,"Romans 8:17; see alsoDoctrine and Covenants 84:38."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,69,"See3 Nephi 28:10."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,70,"Doctrine and Covenants 132:19."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,71,"SeeAlma 28:12;Mormon 7:7."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,72,"The words ofDoctrine and Covenants 58:42are some of the most inspiring and encouraging in scripture: “He who has repented of his sins, the same is forgiven, and I, the Lord, remember them no more.” What joy this gives me to know that if I continue to repent, in that future day when I shall fall on my knees before my Savior and Redeemer, He will lift me up and embrace me. My sins will not only be forgiven; they will not even be remembered."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,73,"SeeLuke 9:35;Joseph Smith—History 1:17."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,74,"SeeAlma 36:17–20."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,75,"See2 Corinthians 5:17."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,76,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 50:24."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,77,"1 John 3:2."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,78,"SeeMormon 7:7."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,79,"John 10:16."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,80,"Doctrine and Covenants 59:5."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,81,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 88:62–63."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,82,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 14:7;41:5."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,83,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 12:8;59:6."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,84,"Doctrine and Covenants 121:45. The process of caring for others allows both rich and poor a way toward refining their characters and leads them both toward exaltation (seeDoctrine and Covenants 104:15–18)."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,85,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 81:5."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,86,"1 John 3:18."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,87,"What qualifies someone to preach the gospel? The Savior answers, “Whosoever will thrust in his sickle and reap, the same is called of God” (Doctrine and Covenants 11:4). Ultimately, it is our desires that qualify us for the work of proclaiming the word of God (seeDoctrine and Covenants 4:3)."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,88,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 124:39."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,89,"Doctrine and Covenants 25:10."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,90,"SeeMosiah 16:11."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,91,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 82:9."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,92,"This was the question the multitude asked Jesus on the banks of the Sea of Galilee. It is a starting question for us as we contemplate becoming disciples of Jesus Christ. (SeeJohn 6:28.)"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,93,"SeeAlma 41:4–5, 10–11."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,94,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 88:63."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,95,"SeeProverbs 3:5."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,96,"See3 Nephi 9:20;Doctrine and Covenants 20:37."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/12uchtdorf,Elder Dieter F. Uchtdorf,97,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 88:63."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,4,"Have you ever wondered why we call Primary “Primary”? While the name refers to spiritual learning children receive in their earliest years, to me it is also a reminder of a powerful truth. To our Heavenly Father, children haveneverbeen secondary—they havealwaysbeen “primary.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,5,"He trusts us to value, respect, and protect them as children of God. That means we never harm them physically, verbally, or emotionally in any way, even when tensions and pressures run high. Instead wevaluechildren, and we do all we can to combat the evils of abuse. Their care is primary to us—as it is to Him."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,6,"One young mother and father sat at their kitchen table reviewing their day. From down the hall, they heard a thud. The mother asked, “What was that?”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,7,"Then they heard a soft cry coming from their four-year-old son’s bedroom. They rushed down the hall. There he was, lying on the floor next to his bed. The mother picked up the little boy and asked him what had happened."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,8,"He said, “I fell out of bed.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,9,"She said, “Why did you fall out of bed?”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,10,"He shrugged and said, “I don’t know. I guess I just didn’t get far enough in.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,11,It is about this “getting far enough in” that I would like to speak this morning. It is our privilege and responsibility to help children “get far enough in” to the gospel of Jesus Christ. And we cannot begin too soon.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,12,"There is a uniquely special time in children’s lives when they are protected from Satan’s influence. It is a time when they are innocent and sin free.It is a sacred time for parent and child. Children are to be taught, by word and example, before and after they have “arrived unto the years of accountability before God.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,13,"President Henry B. Eyring taught: “We have the greatest opportunity with the young. The best time to teach is early, while children are still immune to the temptations of [the] mortal enemy, and long before the words of truth may be harder for them to hear in the noise of their personal struggles.”Such teaching will help them realize their divine identity, their purpose, and the rich blessings that await them as they make sacred covenants and receive ordinances along the covenant path."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,14,"We cannot wait for conversion to simply happen to our children. Accidental conversion isnota principle of the gospel of Jesus Christ. Becoming like our Savior will not happen randomly. Being intentional in loving, teaching, and testifying can help children begin at a young age to feel the influence of the Holy Ghost.The Holy Ghost is essential to our children’s testimony of and conversion to Jesus Christ; we desire them to “always remember him, that they may have his Spirit to be with them.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,15,"Consider the value of family conversations about the gospel of Jesus Christ,essentialconversations, that can invite the Spirit. When we have such conversations with our children, we help them create a foundation, “which is a sure foundation, a foundation whereon if [they] build they cannot fall.”When we strengthen a child, we strengthen the family."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,16,"These vital discussions can lead children to:"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,17,Understand the doctrine of repentance.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,18,"Have faith in Christ, the Son of the living God."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,19,Choose baptism and the gift of the Holy Ghost when eight years old.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,20,And pray and “walk uprightly before the Lord.”
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,21,"The Savior urged, “Therefore I give unto you a commandment, to teach these thingsfreelyunto your children.”And what did He want us to teach so freely?"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,22,The Fall of Adam
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,23,The Atonement of Jesus Christ
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,24,The importance of being born again
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,25,"Elder D. Todd Christofferson said, “Certainly the adversary is pleased when parents neglect to teach and train their children to have faith in Christ and be spiritually born again.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,26,"In contrast, the Savior would have us help children “put [their] trust in that Spirit which leadeth to do good.”To do so, we can assist children in recognizing when they are feeling the Spirit and in discerning what actions cause the Spirit to leave. Thus they learn to repent and return to the light through the Atonement of Jesus Christ. This helps encourage spiritual resilience."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,27,"We can have fun helping our children build spiritual resilience at any age. It doesn’t have to be complicated or time intensive. Simple, caring conversations can lead children to know not onlywhatthey believe, but most important,whythey believe it. Caring conversations, happening naturally and consistently, can lead to better understanding and answers. Let’s not allow the convenience of electronic devices to keep us from teaching and listening to our children and looking into their eyes."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,28,"Additional opportunities for essential conversations can occur through role-playing. Family members can act out situations of being tempted or pressured to make a bad choice. Such an exercise can fortify children to be prepared in a challenging setting. For example, we can act it out and then talk it out as we ask children what they would do:"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,29,If they are tempted to break the Word of Wisdom.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,30,If they are exposed to pornography.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,31,"If they are tempted to lie, steal, or cheat."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,32,If they hear something from a friend or teacher at school that disputes their beliefs or values.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,33,"As they act it out and then talk it out, rather than being caught unprepared in a hostile peer group setting, children can be armed with “the shield of faith wherewith [they] shall be able to quenchallthe fiery darts of the wicked.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,34,A close personal friend learned this crucial lesson as an 18-year-old. He enlisted in the United States military during the conflict between the United States and Vietnam. He was assigned to basic training in the infantry to become a foot soldier. He explained that the training was grueling. He described his drill instructor as cruel and inhumane.
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,35,"One particular day his squad was dressed in full battle gear, hiking in sweltering heat. The drill instructor suddenly shouted orders to drop to the ground and not move. The instructor was watching for even theslightestmotion. Any movement would result in serious consequences later on. The squad suffered for more than two hours in the heat with growing anger and resentment toward their leader."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,36,"Many months later our friend found himself leading his squad through the jungles of Vietnam. This was real, not just training. Shots began to ring from high in the surrounding trees. The entire squad immediately dropped to the ground."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,37,"What was the enemy looking for? Movement. Any motion at all would draw fire. My friend said that as he lay sweating and motionless on the jungle floor, waiting for dark for several long hours, his thoughts reflected back on basic training. He remembered his intense dislike for his drill instructor. Now he felt intense gratitude—for what he had taught him and how he had prepared him for this critical situation. The drill instructor had wisely equipped our friend and his squad with the ability to know what to do when the battle was raging. He had, in effect, saved our friend’s life."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,38,"How can we do the same for our children spiritually? Long before they enter the battlefield of life, how can we more fully strive to teach, fortify, and prepare them?How can we invite them to “get far enough in”? Wouldn’t we rather have them “sweat” in the safe learning environment of the home thanbleed on the battlefields of life?"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,39,"As I look back, there were times when my husband and I felt like drill instructors in our earnestness to help our children live the gospel of Jesus Christ. The prophet Jacob seemed to voice these same feelings when he said: “I am desirous for the welfare of your souls. Yea, mine anxiety is great for you; and ye yourselves know that it ever has been.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,40,"As children learn and progress, their beliefs will be challenged. But as they are properly equipped, they can grow in faith, courage, and confidence, even in the midst of strong opposition."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,41,"Alma taught us to “prepare the minds of [the] children.”We are preparing the rising generation to be the future defenders of the faith, to understand “that [they] are free to act for [themselves]—to choose the way of everlasting death or the way of eternal life.”Children deserve to understand this great truth: eternity is the wrong thing to be wrong about."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,42,"May our simple yet essential conversations with our children help them to “enjoy thewordsof eternal life” now so that they may enjoy “eternal life in the world to come, even immortal glory.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,43,"As we nurture and prepare our children, we allow for their agency, we love them with all our heart, we teach them God’s commandments and His gift of repentance, and we never,ever, give up on them. After all, isn’t this the Lord’s way with each of us?"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,44,"Let us “press forward with a steadfastness in Christ,” knowing that we can have “a perfect brightness of hope”through our loving Savior."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,45,"I testify that He is always the answer. In the sacred name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,46,Notes
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,47,"See3 Nephi 17:23–24."
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,48,"See Michaelene P. Grassli, “Behold Your Little Ones,”Ensign, Nov. 1992, 93: “To me, the wordbeholdis significant. It implies more than just ‘look and see.’ When the Lord instructed the Nephites tobeholdtheir little ones, I believe he told them to give attention to their children, to contemplate them, to look beyond the present and see their eternal possibilities.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,49,"See also Russell M. Nelson, “Listen to Learn,”Ensign, May 1991, 22: “To rule children by force is the technique of Satan, not of the Savior. No, we don’t own our children. Our parental privilege is to love them, to lead them, and to let them go.”"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/13jones,Joy D. Jones,50,"SeeDoctrine and Covenants 29:46–47."
