  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/41soares,Elder Ulisses Soares,29,"Elements of Passover that pointed to the Atonement of Jesus Christ included a sacrificial lamb (seeExodus 12:3, 5, 21), partaking of unleavened bread with bitter herbs (seeExodus 12:8, 15;Leviticus 23:6;Numbers 9:11), blood of the sacrificial lamb being placed on doorposts of homes (seeExodus 12:7, 13, 22–23), and the feast being eaten in haste (seeExodus 12:11)."
