  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/49nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,51,"Without the power of faith, would Abinadi have suffered death by fire for refusing to deny what he knew to be true? (seeMosiah 17:7–20). Without that power, would Ether have hidden in the cavity of a rock (seeEther 13:13–14) and Moroni endured years of loneliness (seeMoroni 1:1–3) when their lives could have been much more comfortable if they had only denounced what they believed?"
  2021,"04",/general-conference/2021/04/49nelson,President Russell M. Nelson,52,"See Melvin L. Bashore, H. Dennis Tolley, and the BYU Pioneer Mortality Team, “Mortality on the Mormon Trail, 1847–1868,”BYU Studies, vol. 53, no. 4 (2014), 115."
